Author-Name: Rohit Varman 
Author-Name: Russell W. Belk 
Title: Nationalism and Ideology in an Anticonsumption Movement 
Abstract:
 In this research we examine the role of the nationalist ideology of
 swadeshi in a contemporary anticonsumption movement and show that its
 deployment is linked to the experiences of colonialism, modernity, and
 globalization in India. Specifically, we offer a postcolonial
 understanding of reflexivity and nationalism in an anticonsumption
 movement opposing Coca-Cola in India. This helps us offer an
 interpretation of this consumer movement involving spatial politics,
 temporal heterogeneity, appropriation of existing ideology, the use of
 consumption in ideology, and attempts to bring together a disparate set of
 actors in the movement. (c) 2009 by JOURNAL OF CONSUMER RESEARCH, Inc.. 
